    scripture: "In every thing give thanks: for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus concerning you.",
    walk: `Friend, here Paul gives us another plainly revealed part of God's will, one we can begin to do this very day: that in everything we give thanks: *In every thing give thanks: for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus concerning you.* Giving thanks in everything is the will of God for us. This teaches us, friend, that God's will is not only about big decisions but about how we live each day, including giving thanks in everything; and this revealed will of God we can begin to do right now.

Consider the call: *In every thing give thanks.* We are to give thanks in everything. Paul calls us to give thanks in everything, friend, in all circumstances, whatever comes. This is a sweeping call, friend, to give thanks not only when things go well, but in everything, in all circumstances, the hard as well as the good. Notice it does not say give thanks *for* everything, friend, as though we must be thankful that evil things happen; it says give thanks *in* everything, in every circumstance, finding cause for thanksgiving to God even in the midst of hard things. This is the call, friend, to give thanks in everything, in all circumstances.

And see that this is God's will: *for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus concerning you.* Giving thanks is God's will for us. Paul tells us plainly, friend, that this is the will of God concerning us: that we give thanks in everything. Here is another place where God's will is plainly revealed, friend, not hidden; it is God's will that we give thanks in everything. We sometimes search anxiously for God's will, friend, regarding our decisions and circumstances, while neglecting the plainly revealed will of God, such as this, that we give thanks in everything. But this is God's will, friend, plainly revealed, that we give thanks in everything.

What does this teach us about seeking God's will, friend? It teaches us that God's will is not only about big decisions but about how we live each day, including giving thanks in everything. We can become so focused on God's will for the big decisions, friend, that we neglect His will for how we live each day, His will that we give thanks in everything, that we be holy, that we love one another. But God's will, friend, is very much about how we live each day, including this, that we give thanks in everything. And this revealed will of God, friend, we can begin to do right now, this very day, giving thanks in everything, in all circumstances. We do not have to wait to discover God's will for our big decisions, friend; we can begin doing His revealed will today, giving thanks in everything.

So give thanks in everything, friend, knowing this is God's will for you, and begin doing this revealed will of God this very day. Do not become so focused on God's will for the big decisions, friend, that you neglect His will for how you live each day, His will that you give thanks in everything. For God's will is very much about how you live each day, friend, including this, that you give thanks in everything, in all circumstances, the hard as well as the good. And this revealed will of God, friend, you can begin to do right now, this very day; you do not have to wait to discover God's will for your big decisions to begin doing His revealed will. So give thanks in everything, friend, in all circumstances, finding cause for thanksgiving to God even in the midst of hard things; for this is the will of God concerning you. So begin today, friend, doing this plainly revealed will of God, giving thanks in everything. For in everything give thanks, for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus concerning you. So give thanks in everything, friend, doing God's revealed will this very day.`,
    prayer: `Lord, thank You for this plainly revealed part of Your will, that I give thanks in everything. Help me not to become so focused on Your will for the big decisions that I neglect Your will for how I live each day, including this, that I give thanks in everything. For Your will is very much about how I live each day, in all circumstances, the hard as well as the good. So help me to give thanks in everything, finding cause for thanksgiving to You even in the midst of hard things. And help me to begin doing this revealed will of God this very day; for I do not have to wait to discover Your will for my big decisions to begin doing Your revealed will. So I will give thanks in everything, doing Your will this very day. For this is Your will in Christ Jesus concerning me. In the name of Jesus Christ. Amen.`,
